Your Role and Responsibilities 
As part of the Security portfolio, IBM MaaS360 is a recognized leader in the Unified Endpoint Management space since 2012 and as the sudden shift to remote work in the past year has exacerbated security challenges the need for faster and more robust UEM adoption has increased. With mobile threat defense (MTD), artificial intelligence (AI) insights, out-of-the-box single sign-on (SSO), multi-factor and passwordless authentication, and conditional access, Mass360 provides the robust risk management posture organizations need without disrupting employee productivity. 
 
IBM is seeking to hire a MaaS360 Technical Sales Specialist. In this role, you will be responsible for solution (MaaS360) and subject matter (endpoint management and security) expertise. The ideal candidate will drive the client technical agenda, account architecture, and technical sales support for IBM MaaS360 across mid-market and enterprise-level accounts. In addition, this employee will help drive business partner training and be part of the critical feedback loop for our offering management team. 
 
Responsibilities include:
 
Accountability for driving client satisfaction such that clients become promoters of the IBM Platform 
Maintaining strong platform and offerings knowledge and articulates the value proposition/ROI, competitive landscape, and relevant use cases to drive sales
 
Application of technical and sales knowledge to create and deliver technical proof points to assist with deal closure including technical presentations, solution workshops, Request for Proposals, product demonstrations, technical education, and Proof of Concepts 
 
Required Technical and Professional Expertise 
 
At least 6 months experience in technical pre-sales 
At least 1 year experience in IT application management, IT support, Technical Sales, or Technical Professional Services 
At least 6 months experience in configuration, integration, testing, and troubleshooting across technical domains 
Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise 
 
At least 2 years experience in B2B technical sales with mobile and/or cloud technology 
At least 2 years experience in technical selling, installing, designing or administering end-to-end mobile device management solutions 
At least 2 years experience in Platform/Operating systems Windows (XP, 7 and Server), MAC, IOS, Android, Blackberry and Linux/DB2 
At least 2 yearsâ€™ experience in Exchange, Lotus Traveler, Active Directory, Certificate Authorities, Networking, Proxy, and/or Blackberry Enterprise Server 
